snippet.title: Travis Kelce's Stylish Nod to Taylor Swift Ahead of Grammy Awards
snippet.description:
In a subtle yet fashionable move, Travis Kelce, the 34-year-old tight end for the Kansas City Chiefs, recently made headlines with his unique wardrobe choice that seemed to pay homage to his girlfriend Taylor Swift. The NFL athlete was spotted in Buffalo, New York, sporting a vibrant mustard yellow suit paired with a multi-colored striped turtleneck and a maroon beanie.

The eye-catching turtleneck immediately drew comparisons to the one worn by Taylor Swift in her 2022 music video, particularly during the 1:19 to 1:52 segment. Although not an exact match, the similarities were enough to catch the attention of fans and media alike.

Travis Kelce's brother, Jason Kelce, couldn't resist poking fun at his sibling's bold fashion statement, humorously suggesting that he looked like he was "auditioning for a new Wes Anderson film."

This isn't the first time the couple has showcased their mutual support. Just last week, Taylor Swift donned a custom Chiefs puffer jacket, mirroring Kelce's iconic red jersey. As we approach the Grammy Awards on February 4, where Swift's hit single "Anti-Hero" is nominated for Song of the Year, Record of the Year, and Best Pop Solo Performance, it seems Kelce is subtly showing his support for his talented girlfriend during this exciting award season.

Stay tuned for more updates on Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift's journey as they continue to make headlines both on and off the field! Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for the latest celebrity news and fashion updates. #TravisKelce #TaylorSwift #GrammyAwards #Fashion #CelebrityNews

snippet.description:
Killer Mike was detained at the Grammy Awards on Sunday after the rapper won three Grammy awards including his first in more than two decades.

In a video, Mike was handcuffed and escorted out by Los Angeles police at Crypto Arena after some joyous moments for him at the Grammys’ Premiere Ceremony on Sunday, where he won three awards in quick succession.

A police spokesperson didn’t offer a name or additional details, but confirmed a Black male was detained.

A representative for Mike did not immediately respond to an emailed or text request for comment. 

The only thing that limits your age is not being truthful about your age or what you’re doing,” the 48-year-old Mike said backstage. He won for best rap performance, rap song and rap album.

“At 20 years old, I thought it was cool to be a drug dealer,” he said. “At 40, I started to live with the regrets and the things I’ve done. At 45, I started to rap about it. At 48, I stand here as a man full of empathy and sympathy for the things I’ve done.”

Mike’s first win came after he won for best rap performance for “Scientists & Engineers,” which also took home best rap song. The single features Andre 3000, Future and Eryn Allen Kane.

He won best rap album for “Michael.”

snippet.title: First Indian to win Grammy Awards #grammys #musicawards #shorts #india
snippet.description:
Pandit Ravi Shankar was a legendary Indian musician and sitar virtuoso who played a significant role in popularizing Indian classical music worldwide. He was a master of the sitar and collaborated with numerous Western musicians, including George Harrison of The Beatles. Shankar's influence extended beyond music, as he was also a composer, teacher, and promoter of Indian culture.

1. **Early Life**: Ravi Shankar was born on April 7, 1920, in Varanasi, India. He came from a Brahmin family of musicians and dancers. His older brother, Uday Shankar, was a famous dancer and choreographer.

2. **Musical Training**: Ravi Shankar began studying music and dance at a young age under the guidance of his brother, Uday Shankar. He also received training in the sitar and Indian classical music from renowned musicians, including Allauddin Khan.

3. **Career**: Shankar gained recognition as a skilled musician and performer in India during the 1940s and 1950s. He toured extensively, both in India and abroad, showcasing his mastery of the sitar and Indian classical music.

4. **Collaborations**: One of Shankar's most notable collaborations was with George Harrison of The Beatles. Their association began in the mid-1960s, and Shankar's influence is evident in songs like "Norwegian Wood" and "Within You Without You." He also collaborated with other Western artists, including Yehudi Menuhin and Philip Glass.

5. **Cultural Ambassador**: Shankar played a crucial role in introducing Indian classical music to the West and promoting cross-cultural understanding through music. He performed at prestigious venues such as the Woodstock Festival and the Monterey Pop Festival.

6. **Legacy**: Ravi Shankar's legacy extends beyond his music. He was a respected teacher, passing on his knowledge and expertise to future generations of musicians. He also received numerous awards and honors throughout his lifetime, including multiple Grammy Awards and India's highest civilian honor, the Bharat Ratna.

7. **Personal Life**: Shankar was married multiple times and had children, including the renowned sitarist Anoushka Shankar. He passed away on December 11, 2012, in San Diego, California, leaving behind a rich musical legacy that continues to inspire musicians worldwide.

snippet.title: Inside the #GRAMMYHouse during the #GRAMMYsNextGen party before the #GRAMMY awards #Hollywood #music
snippet.description:
~Lady Lila Brown takes you inside the #GRAMMYHouse with friends 
•••
The @RecordingAcademy #GRAMMY House returned for a second consecutive year for music makers, culture creators and rising industry leaders to participate in three program-packed days leading up to the 66th Annual GRAMMY Awards® airing Sun, Feb. 4 on CBS and Paramount+. GRAMMY House is presented by Mastercard and runs from Thurs, Feb. 1, 2024, to Sat, Feb. 3, 2024, in Los Angeles. As a longtime sponsor of the #GRAMMYs, Mastercard is committed to connecting consumers to their passion for music and continues to be a dedicated supporter of the music industry, artists, fans as well as programs for emerging artists.

The third annual #GRAMMYsNextGen Party for leading creators and professionals who are shaping the future of music, presented by Mastercard and Dyson. The party will feature live performances by first-time GRAMMY nominee Romy, Blaqbonez, Cyanide Beats, and DJ Yasmin. As guests arrive on the red carpet they will experience music amplified by Sonos, and enjoy photo opportunities, light bites, food trucks, and refreshments. Guests can visit the Mastercard Secret Garden and Bloom House Speakeasy to learn more about their Priceless Planet Coalition initiative. Dyson will provide a pure, immersive listening experience, with opportunities to trial and capture content of the brand’s first audio technology, the Dyson Zone™ noise-cancelling headphones. In addition, Dyson styling stations will be available for on-site touch ups and hands on access to its full range of haircare technology. #Hollywood #music #party #socialite #fun #dance #friends #musicindustry #musicbusiness

snippet.title: Nigerian Artists Lose Out On The 2024 Grammy Awards. Davido Reacts
snippet.description:
Nigerian Artists Lose Out On The 2024 Grammy Awards


In the 66th edition of the Grammy Awards, none of the ten Nigerian artists nominated across five categories secured a win. Afrobeats stars including Burna Boy, Davido, Tems, Ayra Starr, Olamide, and Asake faced disappointment as they lost in various categories. The inaugural 'Best African Music Performance' trophy went to South African singer Tyla for her 2023 track, "Water," while Burna Boy and Davido missed out on the Best Global Music Performance category, won by Indian composer Zakir Hussain.


Additionally, Lil Durk's collaboration with J Cole, "All My Life," thwarted Burna Boy's chances of winning any of his four nominations, claiming the Grammy for Best Melodic Rap. Tems, who won a Grammy last year in the same category, faced disappointment this year, losing in the Song Written for Visual Media category. Despite the absence of Nigerian victories, the Grammy Awards showcased performances from music's biggest stars, with comedian Trevor Noah returning as the host for the fourth consecutive year. SZA, with nine nominations, dominated the event, but her sole win prior to this year was for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance in 2022 for "Kiss Me More."

snippet.title: Grammy Awards 2024: Taylor Swift makes history with fourth album of the year win
snippet.description:
A big night for women at the 66th Annual Grammy Awards, as female artistes Taylor Swift, Miley Cyrus and SZA took home top prizes. Swift set another music industry record on Sunday, taking home the coveted album of the year award for the fourth time. SZA, who led all Grammy nominees this year with nine nods, and was reportedly neck and neck with Swift for Album of the Year, won best R&B song for 'Snooze'.

snippet.title: Diplo und Victoria Monet über AI bei Grammy Awards 2024 #grammyawards2024 #aimusic #victoriamonet
snippet.description:
Grammy Awards 2024: Diplo, David Guetta und Victoria Monet sprechen über AI.
Künstler diskutieren KI auf den Grammys.

Bei den diesjährigen Grammys teilten bekannte Künstler und Produzenten ihre Meinung zur künstlichen Intelligenz. 

Diplo findet, man solle Technik nutzen, aber immer die Kontrolle behalten. 

I think when it comes to someone in the background, like production, say for instance, I can’t afford a choir. I can do and AI choir, I can do some AI. I’ve been a studio and you write some lyrics. You have them tailored by AI – utilize it, you know. But make sure you have control. And when it comes down to the branding, the person always matters. But all your tools are useful, so use all of them.”

Victoria Monét meint, KI könne hilfreich sein, wenn fair entlohnt. 

But, yeah, I’m not – I’m like, kind of in the middle. If we can get a grip on the legal parts. I think AI can be really strong.” (Zeige Image)

snippet.title: 💥 TUDO SOBRE O VESTIDO DOURADO DA MILEY CYRUS NO GRAMMY AWARDS 2024 | @sitedacris P/ Cris Cardoso
snippet.description:
A internet quer saber e meu DM no instagram bombou: qual era o tecido do vestido metálico dourado da Miley Cyrus no Grammy Awards 2024? Pois bem, cá está!

Além de conquistar seu primeiro Grammy esse ano com 'Flowers', Miley Cyrus faturou o coração da internet inteirinha com suas aparições triunfais. Ao todo, foram 5 trocas de looks na noite.

De todos, o que fez a internet tombar foi o dourado, com o qual ela triunfou no tapete vermelho e surpreendeu geral: o vestido produzido exclusivamente para ela pela Maison Margiela foi feito com 14.000 alfinetes dourados. Você não leu errado: catorze mil.

Foram 675 horas de trabalho.

O vestido metálico tinha forma de rede que lembrava uma melindrosa da década de 1920 e, ao mesmo tempo, uma deusa egípcia em um trabalho realmente primoroso. John Galliano foi o diretor criativo que elaborou o look e muitos internautas não deixaram de notar a semelhança do vestido da Miley com as peças da coleção prêt-à-porter dele, do outono de 1997.

Para a beleza, o cabelo detalhadamente preparado pelo cabeleireiro Bob Recine criou cachos mais dramáticos e a gente não poderia deixar de associar os penteados de Farrah Fawcett. “No ano passado, apresentei o look de cabelo molhado de Miley”, “Este ano decidimos que queríamos algo seco e maior… cabelo mais cheio, mas sexy, despenteado e palpável.” ele disse em comunicado à imprensa.

Já a maquiagem foi trabalhada por James Kaliardos em tons dourados com acabamento brilhante. Em um post no Insta, Kaliardos disse que queria ela Cyrus “brilhasse como uma deusa dourada, sublime, com pele transparente, acabamento brilhante, uma beleza palpável”.

Atuei por mais de 22 anos como Estrategista de Marcas, Gestora de Comunicação, Marketing, Branding e Treinamentos em Empresas Startups de Tecnologia, Telecom e como jornalista e editora de Moda, Beleza e Comportamento, desde 2009.

Criei minha primeira empresa nativo-digital em 2009 (marca de acessórios com operação nacional e revenda internacional em NY e Grécia) e, por causa da marca, o criscardoso.com foi fundado.

Hoje, sou diretora-executiva, estrategista de marca e criativa da marca Cris Cardoso, do Hub de Cursos, Mentorias e Conteúdos Ponto de Performance e do Hub de Cursos, Atendimentos e Conteúdos Energia da Semana. 

Continuo atuando como docente convidada do Senac e Consultora para Planejamento de Presença Digital para Empreendedores, pelo Sebrae.

Tenho 2 núcleos digitais focados em literatura:  @letrinhanaestante  e  @letranaestante  

Sou de Niterói, no RJ e vivo em SP.

Obrigada por estar aqui.
Com amor,
Cris

snippet.title: Why Grammy Awards Can Be Unpredictable
snippet.description:
Predicting who will win at the Grammys is not straightforward. There are committees, back-room conversations, vote-splitting, and we have no idea how close a race really is.

In 2022, Jon Batiste won Album Of The Year despite having the lowest betting odds among all the albums that were nominated. 

In this episode of Trapital, I’m joined by Zack O'Malley Greenburg to explore the business behind the Grammys, its cultural impact, the major controversies over the years, and so much more. 

Watch the full episode: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Rnj6c4_oD74

snippet.title: Grammys Gone WILD! Adele's CRAZY Stunt Makes Beyonce & Everyone Else GASP!
snippet.description:
Click to subscribe: https://www.youtube.com/@nextremedynews?sub_confirmation=1

Step back in time to the unforgettable 2017 Grammys, a night where Adele left an indelible mark on the music industry. Join us as we countdown the Top 10 moments that defined her golden night, from unexpected twists to tear-jerking performances. 🏆🎤

In the first spot, witness the emotional rollercoaster of Adele's Grammy speech, where she poured her heart out about motherhood, self-discovery, and the joy of reconnecting with her music. 🌟 Then, dive into the mystery of "The Monkey" moment and relive the Queen B homage that had the world buzzing.

Key Takeaways:

Emotional Rollercoaster: Experience the raw and emotional side of Adele as she reflects on motherhood, self-discovery, and the joy of reconnecting with her music during her Grammy speech.

The Monkey Mystery: Unravel the mystery surrounding "The Monkey" moment – a quirky incident during Adele's Album of the Year acceptance speech that caused a global buzz, showcasing the unpredictability of live events.

Queen B Homage: Witness Adele's bold declaration of Beyoncé as the artist of her life, transcending typical acceptance speeches and highlighting genuine admiration and respect among music icons.

Backstage Dream Team: Acknowledge the unsung heroes – Adele's production team. Explore the collaborative effort behind her magic, emphasizing the importance of teamwork in the music industry.

"Hello from the Other Side:" Relive the nostalgia of Adele's iconic "Hello" performance, transforming the Grammy stage into a cozy living room and showcasing the global phenomenon of the song.

#Adele #Grammys2017 #MusicHistory #AdeleMoments #GrammysCountdown #EmotionalPerformances #QueenB #HelloPerformance #GrammysGoldRush #SongwriterOfTheYear #AdeleTop10 #MusicLegends

snippet.title: Jay-Z critique les Grammy Awards en défendant Beyoncé #rapusa #jayz #beyonce #grammysawards
snippet.description: Salut à tous les rappeurs et rappeuses fans de musique ! Bienvenue sur la chaîne Cherif du Rap, votre source incontournable pour suivre l'actualité brûlante du monde du rap. Dans cette vidéo, nous allons parler de trois événements marquants qui ont secoué la scène rap ces derniers jours. Tout d'abord, Jay-Z, le magnat du rap, n'a pas hésité à critiquer les Grammy Awards pour leur manque de reconnaissance envers Beyoncé. Ensuite, le rappeur incontournable Booba nous annonce l'arrivée prochaine d'un nouveau projet intitulé "Ad Vitam Æternam". Enfin, nous verrons le moment émouvant où MHD a célébré sa libération entouré de ses proches. Alors, attachez vos ceintures, la vidéo commence maintenant !"

snippet.title: Keseruan Raisa Menghadiri Grammy Awards 2024 di Los Angeles
snippet.description:
Ajang penghargaan musik terbesar di dunia, Grammy Awards 2024, sukses digelar di Los Angeles pada Minggu, 4 Januari 2024. Sederet musisi ternama dunia turut meramaikan acara tersebut. Sebut saja Mariah Carey, Billie Eilish, hingga Taylor Swift. 
Raisa rupanya juga ikut menghadiri acara tersebut. Ia menjadi satu-satunya perwakilan Indonesia di event tersebut. Raisa tampil stunning mengenakan dress panjang berwarna merah maroon. Pelantun Kali Kedua ini membagikan momen-momen dirinya saat menghadiri Grammy 2024 lewat Instagram Story.

snippet.title: Harmonizing Success: Insights from a Six-Time Grammy Award-Winning Producer & Label CEO
snippet.description:
Paki & Chris invite CEO of Straight Lace Entertainment @straightlaceent, International GT @internationalgt & Multi Grammy Award Winning Mixing Engineer James “Bonzai” Caruso @bonzaicaruso, to join the CIRCLE for Episode 134.

Click the LINK in BIO to watch the full Episode at TheVegasCircle.com. Also avail on all podcast audio outlets.

International GT, the Las Vegas-based multi-talent in the rap game, boasts a unique journey from earning a recording arts degree at Full Sail University to becoming a staff engineer at Patchwerk Recording Studios in Atlanta, GA. Collaborating with heavyweights like Young Thug, George Clinton, Fetty Wap, and 21 Savage, GT's unmistakable flow and signature vocal effects bring a fresh flavor to modern Hip-Hop. With a Grammy-nominated album and RIAA Gold Certification under his belt, GT's success is undeniable. From his debut album "Elevation" to the recently dropped "NIGHT OF THE WIN!" and the mind-bending "T.I.M.E." in 2022, International GT proves that "True Imagination Makes Everything."

James "Bonzai" Caruso, a six-time Grammy-winning sonic wizard with over three decades of experience, kicks off his legendary journey as a teenage prodigy at the Institute of Audio Research in Greenwich Village. By his early 20s, Bonzai was already making waves in NYC's top studios, credited with revolutionizing sounds for icons like Grand Master Flash, Melle Mell, Africa Bambatta, and Ice T. His mixing prowess caught the attention of legends like Sean "Puffy" Combs, Mary J. Blige, Notorious B.I.G., Missy Elliot, and more. Bonzai's magic touch extends to chart-toppers with Stephen Marley, shaping hits like "Welcome to Jamrock" and "Distant Relatives." From Alicia Keys to Mariah Carey, Gwen Stefani to Lenny Kravitz, Bonzai's sonic palette transcends genres. Beyond artists, he crafts original scores for films and TV, leaving his indelible mark on campaigns for Phillip Morris, CMT, Adidas, and more.

अमेरिकेमध्ये 66 वा ग्रॅमी सोहळा पार पडला आहे. यंदा या मानाच्या पुरस्कार सोहळ्यामध्ये भारतीय कलाकारांनीही विजेतेपद पटकावत देशाची मान उंचावली आहे. Zakir Hussain यांनी ग्रॅमीत यंदा एका रात्रीत 3 पुरस्कार पटकावून नवा विक्रम रचला आहे,  जाणून घ्या अधिक माहिती

#Grammys2024Winners #Grammys2024 #TaylorSwift #MileyCyrus #ShankarMahadevan #ZakirHussain #Grammys2024WinnersFullList

snippet.title: Grammy Awards : Taylor Swift bat un record avec l'album de l'année pour la 4ème fois • FRANCE 24
snippet.description:
Elle est entrée dans l'histoire des Grammy Awards, l'équivalent musical des Oscars. Taylor Swift a remporté, dimanche 4 février, le prix de l'album de l'année, considéré comme la récompense reine, pour la quatrième fois de sa carrière. Avec cet honneur attribué à son disque Midnights, la chanteuse américaine s'inscrit ainsi au panthéon de la cérémonie comme l'artiste la plus récompensée pour ses albums, devant Frank Sinatra, Stevie Wonder et Paul Simon.
#Taylor Swift #Grammy #musique

snippet.title: Céline Dion makes surprise appearance at Grammy Awards

Céline Dion arrived onstage at the end of the 66th Grammy Awards to present the final award of the night, album of the year, to Taylor Swift. It was a rare public appearance by the singer, who has been on hiatus from live performances following her diagnosis with stiff person syndrome.

snippet.title: Blue Ivy Looks SO Grown Up w/ Beyoncé & Jay-Z At 2024 Grammy Awards
snippet.description: It was a family affair for the Carters at the 2024 Grammy Awards! Blue Ivy joined her parents, Beyoncé and Jay-Z, at music's biggest night on Sunday and looked all grown up in an off the shoulder white midi dress with a princess-like draped skirt. The 12-year-old joined her dad on-stage as he received the second annual Dr. Dre Global Impact Award, which honors his impactful legacy in music, and proudly looked up at the rapper as he gave her a shoutout while accepting the award. When Blue wasn't on stage she was posing with Olivia Rodrigo and enjoying the show next to her parents.

snippet.title: Words Have Meanings and can lead you to the Grammy Awards- Queen Sheba
snippet.description:
Leslie Shorthost of Visibility Ultd. podcast and owner of The Cavu Group interviews Grammy-nominated Artist for Best Spoken Word Poetry Album guest Queen Sheba. She will also share the difference between Poetry and Spoken word. She shares how her journey to the Grammy's began and having a hand in pushing for Spoken Word to be its own category. 


Social Impact is where Spoken Word lives as people share their stories about places, people, and things.

snippet.title: Burna Boy devient le premier artiste africain annoncé au 66e Grammy Awards 2024
snippet.description:
#burnaboy #grammyawards2024 #afrobeats #nigeriamusic 

Le chanteur nigérian Burna Boy devient le premier artiste africain annoncé au 66e Grammy Awards

 Dans une annonce faite lundi dernier 22 janvier 2024,  Burna Boy a été cité parmi les artistes qui se produiront sur la scène des Grammy Awards 2024.

Burna Boy s’est imposé comme l’un des artistes les plus influents de sa génération. Son style musical unique, métissé d' afrobeat, dancehall et reggae, a conquis les cœurs du public mondial, faisant de lui une véritable icône de la musique africaine contemporaine.

La nouvelle de la performance de Burna Boy aux Grammy Awards a été accueillie avec enthousiasme par ses fans 

Sa performance marquera un tournant majeur pour l’industrie musicale africaine.

Ce chanteur nigérian de renom prestera  aux côtés d’autres artistes de renom tels que Travis Scott, Billie Eilish, Olivia Rodrigo et Luke Combs .

snippet.title: Why Killer Mike Was Arrested After Winning 3 Grammy Awards, He Was Taken Away in Handcuffs.

snippet.title: Does winning the most Grammy Awards equate to winning Album of the Year?
snippet.description:
If you watched the 66th annual Grammy Awards on Sunday night, you heard Jay-Z call out the awards show while accepting the Dr. Dre Global Impact Award, specifically related to Beyoncé never winning its Album of the Year honor, so we're checking the facts behind his claim. 

"The most Grammys," he said, referencing Beyoncé's 32 Grammy Awards won over the course of her music career, to date. "Never won album of the year. That doesn't work."

Beyoncé has won those awards for her solo work, work with Destiny’s Child and under work the group name, The Carters, which she and husband Jay-Z completed together. That’s the most Grammy Awards any artist has ever won.

Read more about this VERIFY: https://www.wkyc.com/article/news/verify/winning-most-grammy-awards-not-equate-album-of-year-verify/95-81b789de-eb91-4dd4-be1e-90635a52ecee --

snippet.title: 2024 NFL Super Bowl LVIII halftime show artist lineup confirmed: Grammy Award-winners and more
snippet.description:
USHER has been announced as the headliner for the 2024 Apple Music Super Bowl LVIII halftime show.

The eight-time Grammy Award-winner was confirmed to headline through a statement from the NFL, Apple Music, and Roc Nation early Sunday morning.

Super Bowl LVIII is set to take place on February 11, 2024, at Allegiant Stadium, home of the Las Vegas Raiders, per The Hollywood Reporter.

Usher called the opportunity an "honor of a lifetime" in a statement.

"It’s an honor of a lifetime to finally check a Super Bowl performance off my bucket list," the singer-songwriter said.

"I can’t wait to bring the world a show unlike anything else they’ve seen from me before."

He added: "Thank you to the fans and everyone who made this opportunity happen. I’ll see you real soon.”

It won't be the first time Usher appeared in a Super Bowl halftime show.

At Super Bowl XLV in 2011, in which the Green Bay Packers took home the famed Vince Lombardi Trophy, Usher made a guest appearance alongside the Black Eyed Peas.

Seth Dudowsky, NFL’s head of music, noted that the league "couldn't be more excited" to have Usher on board for Super Bowl LVIII.

"Usher is an icon whose music has left an indelible mark on the cultural landscape throughout his career, we couldn’t be more excited to have him headline this year’s Apple Music Super Bowl Halftime Show,” he told THR.

“We look forward to working with Usher, Roc Nation, and Apple Music to bring fans another Halftime Show for the history books.”

Vice President of Apple Music, Apple TV+, and Sports, Oliver Schusser, noted a similar sentiment.

“We are so proud of what we were able to accomplish together with the NFL and Roc Nation last year, and now, with the insanely talented Usher set to take the stage, we’re looking forward to another incredible Halftime Show from one of the world’s all-time greatest performers," he said.

Apple Music also made a tease of the announcement to X, formerly Twitter, on Sunday.

The post featured a skit of Kim Kardashian calling to break the big news to Usher.

Jay-Z and his entertainment company, Roc Nation, are back again to produce the halftime event for the fifth year in a row.

The famed rapper and entrepreneur, who has a staggering 24 Grammy Awards of his own, spoke highly of Usher after the headliner announcement.

“Usher is the ultimate artist and showman," Jay-Z said, per THR.

"Ever since his debut at the age of 15, he’s been charting his own unique course."

He continued: "Beyond his flawless singing and exceptional choreography, Usher bares his soul."

“His remarkable journey has propelled him to one of the grandest stages in the world. I can’t wait to see the magic.”

Usher and Jay-Z collaborated on records like Best Thing, Hottie Tottie, and Anything over the years.

Usher is currently starting the Rendez-Vous Á Paris at La Seine Musicale eight-night residency in Paris, France.

snippet.title: Grammy Awards 2024: Zakir Hussain And Shakti Win Big
snippet.description:
Indian percussionist Zakir Hussain and flutist Rakesh Chaurasia have won big at the 2024 Grammy Awards.

Their song Pashto, which was awarded, features American musicians Bela Fleck and Edgar Meyer.

The category included Falu's Abundance In Millets featuring Prime Minister Narendra Modi among the nominees and Shadow Forces by Arooj Aftab and Vijay Iyer.

snippet.title: Grammy Awards Honour the Super Nova Music Festival Victims
snippet.description:
"Everyone of us, no matter where we're from, is united by the shared experience of music. It brings us together, like nothing else can. And that's why music must always be our safe space. When that is violated, it strikes at the very core of who we are ... On October 7, we felt that again when we heard the tragic news from the Supernova music festival for love, that over 360 music fans lost their lives, and another 40 were kidnapped."

Recording Academy CEO Harvey Mason Jr. delivered this moving speech at the 2024 Grammy's, honouring the victims of the Super Nova Music Festival, who were murdered and kidnapped by Hamas Terrorists on 7 October. 

We thank Harvey for sharing this powerful message.

#StandwithIsrael #SuperNova #BringThemHomeNOW

snippet.title: 36th Annual Grammy Awards
snippet.description:
The 36th Annual Grammy Awards were held on March 1, 1994. They recognized accomplishments by musicians from the previous year. Whitney Houston was the Big Winner winning 3 awards including Record of the Year and Album of the Year while opening the show with "I Will Always Love You".
Audrey Hepburn's win made her the fifth person to become an EGOT, and the first person to complete the status posthumously.
Paul Simon was the first performer of the evening.

Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/36th_Annual_Grammy_Awards

Welcome to the Grammy night that redefined Adele's legacy! Join us on a journey through the highs and lows of her monumental 25 album, as we unveil the untold stories behind each epic moment. From emotional returns to record-breaking wins, this video is your backstage pass to the heart of Adele's reign as music royalty.

Adele's emotional return: After a hiatus focused on motherhood, Adele's raw vulnerability on stage resonated deeply with viewers.
Record-breaking wins: "25" dominated the night, claiming Album, Record, and Song of the Year, solidifying Adele's place in music history.
Unseen performances: Witness the world premiere of "When We Were Young" and an intimate "Million Years Ago" rendition straight from her kitchen.
Musical evolution: From humble beginnings in London pubs to Grammy glory, Adele showcased her diverse musical journey through stripped-down and powerful arrangements.
Universal connection: Songs like "All I Ask" transcended genres and generations, sparking collective catharsis and reminding us of shared human experiences.
Memorable moments: Tears, triumphs, epic speeches, and unexpected surprises – this video is a treasure trove of unforgettable moments from Adele's 25 Grammys night.

snippet.title: Watch Dr. Dre Accept The Inaugural Global Impact Award, Named In His Honor | GRAMMY Rewind

snippet.title: Jay Z calls out Beyoncé snubs at GRAMMYs 🎙️✨
snippet.description:
Jay Z paid tribute to his wife Beyoncé while accepting the Dr. Dre Global Impact Award at the 66th GRAMMY Awards. "She has more Grammys than everybody and never won album of the year," he said, calling out the Recording Academy. "So even by your own metrics, that doesn’t work. Think about that: The most Grammys. Never won album of the year. That doesn’t work."

snippet.title: BURNA BOY AWEKA REKODI MPYA GRAMMY AWARDS
snippet.description:
Big News kwa mashabiki wa Damibe Ebunoluwa Ogulu AkA The African Giant Burnboy ametajwa kuperforme katika  tuzo za Grammy 2023 siku ya Jumapili ya February 4, pande za Los Angeles Marekani.

Burnaboy ataweka rekodi mpya ya kuwa msanii wa kwanza kutoka Africa kufanya show katika tuzo hizo za Grammy zinazofanyika kwa mara ya 66.

Pia yupo katika vipengele vinne anavyoshindania katika tuzo hizo ambazo ni Best African Music Performance, Best Global Music Performance, Best Melodic Rap Performance na Best Global Music Album. 

Ikubukwe mwaka 2021 Burnboy alishinda Grammy Awards kwenye kipengere cha Best Global Music Album kupitia Album yake ya Twice as Tall.

Msanii mwingine ambaye ataperforme siku ya tuzo hizo ni Travis Scott ambaye ni anawania kipengele cha Album Bora ya Mwaka.
#burnaboy #afropop #afropopmusic

snippet.title: Grammy Winning Record Every Year (1959-2024)
snippet.description:
This video goes through each year of the Grammys showing which songs won the Record of the Year award. 

Record of the Year is awarded for a single or for one track from an album. This award goes to the performing artist, the producer, recording engineer and/or mixer for that song. In this sense, "record" means a particular recorded song, not its composition or an album of songs.

This differs from the Song of the Year, Song of the Year is also awarded for a single or individual track, but the recipient of this award is the songwriter who actually wrote the lyrics and/or melodies to the song. "Song" in this context means the song as composed, not its recording.

Thanks for watching! Check out some other videos on the channel:

snippet.title: Grammy Performance Chaos - Playing Guitar for Lady A
snippet.description:
Please subscribe for weekly episodes with your favorite musicians, entertainers and athletes!

In this exciting clip from the Nashtyville Podcast, special guest Slim Gambill, the renowned lead guitarist for the Grammy-winning, multi-platinum country group Lady A, shares a heart-stopping moment from one of his performances at the Grammy Awards. 

Gambill recalls the tension-filled incident that occurred during a commercial break, just moments before a live acoustic performance was set to begin. As he was tuning his guitar, a string suddenly snapped, putting the performance in jeopardy. With the clock ticking and the pressure mounting, a quick-thinking stagehand rushes to his aid, providing a new guitar just in the nick of time. 

This story is a thrilling glimpse into the behind-the-scenes drama of live music performances at high-stakes events like the Grammys. Listen as Slim Gambill brings this memorable experience to life, showcasing the unpredictability and excitement of live music.

snippet.title: The Grammy Award for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance 2012 - 2024
snippet.description:
The Grammy Award for Record of the Year is presented by the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences of the United States to "honor artistic achievement, technical proficiency and overall excellence in the recording industry, without regard to sales or chart position. The Record of the Year award is one of the four "General Field" categories at the awards (alongside Best New Artist, Song of the Year and Album of the Year) presented annually since the 1st Annual Grammy Awards in 1959.
.
Record of the Year is awarded for a single or for one track from an album. This award goes to the performing artist, the producer, recording engineer and/or mixer for that song. In this sense, "record" means a particular recorded song, not its composition or an album of songs.
.
Lady Gaga and SZA are the only acts overall to win this category multiple times, both with two wins. Coldplay are the act with most nominations in this category, receiving a total of five nods, but they have yet to win in this category.
.
Hope you enjoy this hit list of Record of the Year from 2000 - 2024 at the Grammy Award
.
.
.

snippet.title: Artists Who Won Their Very First Grammy At The 66th Grammy Awards 2024
snippet.description:
Artists Winning Their first Grammy , First Time Grammy Winners At the 66th Annual Grammys , Miley Cyrus - Tyla - Karol G  - Victoria Monet - Phoebe Bridgers First Grammy Win ,  Artists That Won Their Very First Grammy At The 66 Grammys, Artists You Didn't Know Won Their First Grammy in 2024, Artists who won their first Grammys at the 66th Annual Grammys, 66th Annual Grammys, Miley Cyrus Grammys, Miley Cyrus 2024 Grammys, Tyla Grammys, Tyla 2024 Grammys, Victoria Monet Grammys, Karol G Grammys, Phoebe Bridgers Grammys, Karol G 2024 Grammys, Phoebe Bridgers 2024 Grammys,66th Grammys


Miley Cyrus took home two awards for ‘Record of The Year’ and ‘Best Pop Solo Performance’ for her hit single ‘Flowers.’ , 

Tyla also won her first ever Grammy for the Best African Music Performance, 

Karol G also secured her first Grammy win for the Best Música Urbana Album., 

Victoria Monet walked away with three awards for the Best New Artist, Best R&B Album and Best Engineered Album, Non-Classical for ‘Jaguar II’, 

Phoebe Bridgers emerged as the night's biggest winner, taking home four Grammys for the Best Pop Duo/Group Performance, Best Rock Performance, Best Rock Song and Best Alternative Music Album.

snippet.title: Taylor Swift Reveals NEW ALBUM Date In 2024 Grammy Awards Speech
snippet.description: Are you ready for it? There's a new Taylor Swift album on the way, and it isn't "Reputation (Taylor's Version)." "I want to say thank you to the fans, by telling you a secret that I've been keeping from you for the past two years. Which is that my brand new album comes out April 19. It's called 'The Tortured Poets Department,'" she revealed on stage. The special announcement came as Taylor was accepting home her 13th Grammy Award for Best Pop Vocal Album. She followed up the big news by revealing the album's cover art and some lyrics on her Instagram. Taylor's big news came a surprise to fans, who thought the singer was getting ready to re-release "Reputation" after she changed the profile pictures on all her social media accounts and rocked a black-and-white dress on the red carpet.

 Dans une annonce faite lundi dernier 22 janvier 2024,  Burna Boy a été cité parmi les artistes qui se produiront sur la scène des Grammy Awards 2024.

Burna Boy s’est imposé comme l’un des artistes les plus influents de sa génération. Son style musical unique, métissé d' afrobeat, dancehall et reggae, a conquis les cœurs du public mondial, faisant de lui une véritable icône de la musique africaine contemporaine.

La nouvelle de la performance de Burna Boy aux Grammy Awards a été accueillie avec enthousiasme par ses fans 

Sa performance marquera un tournant majeur pour l’industrie musicale africaine.

Ce chanteur nigérian de renom prestera  aux côtés d’autres artistes de renom tels que Travis Scott, Billie Eilish, Olivia Rodrigo et Luke Combs .

snippet.title: INDIA Shines at Grammy Awards 2024 : "Best Global Music Album Award" #grammyawards2024 #india
snippet.description:
February, 5th Grammy Awards 2024: The 66th Annual Grammy Awards 2024 are being held in Los Angeles. Indian Ace musicians Shankar Mahadevan and Zakir Hussain's fusion band ‘Shakti’ bagged the Grammy's award for ‘Best Global Music Album’ on Monday. The award was for their latest album ‘This Moment’.
The Magical Maestro's Ustad Zakir Hussian and Shankar Mahadevan brings laurels by winning the prestigious Grammy.

snippet.title: TYLA WINS BEST AFRICAN MUSIC PERFORMANCE AT THE GRAMMY AWARDS 2024
snippet.description:
Tyla, the talented artist, achieved a significant milestone by winning her inaugural Grammy award in the category of Best African Music Performance for her captivating song titled "WATER." This accomplishment marks a remarkable moment in her burgeoning career, showcasing her unique talent and dedication to African music. 

Tyla's win not only recognizes her exceptional performance but also highlights the cultural richness and diversity of African music on the global stage. With this prestigious accolade, Tyla's musical journey is poised for further recognition and success, inspiring audiences worldwide with her soulful melodies and evocative performances.
#tyla_water #tylawater #grammyawards

snippet.title: 2023 Music Industry Grad Nominated for GRAMMY Award
snippet.description:
🌟 Exciting News! 🎶 SUNY Oneonta alumna Elyse Victoria Johnson, who graduated in December 2023 with a degree in Music Industry, is going to the GRAMMYs! 🎤 Elyse was nominated as a songwriter for the uplifting Gospel anthem “God is Good.”  🙌 We’ll be cheering for Elyse and her talented collaborators on Sunday, Feb. 4, during the 66th Annual Grammy Awards.

Read more about Elyse's journey here:
https://suny.oneonta.edu/news-events/2023-music-industry-grad-nominated-grammy-award

🔥 #GRAMMYs #GodIsGood #MusicIndustry #ElyseVictoriaJohnson

snippet.title: Why Davido May not Win the 2024 Grammy Awards
snippet.description:
Why Davido May not Win the 2024 Grammy Awards

No doubt, Davido was nominated for the 2024 Grammy awards. The list includes other Nigerian artists like Burna Boy, Ayra Starr, Fireboy, Seun Kuti, Tems, Asake, and Olamide. These Nigerian Musicians did their best in the past year and bagged Grammy nominations. Davido bagged three Grammy nominations while Burna Boy had four Grammy nominations. Recall that Burna Boy won best global music album for Twice as Tall in 2021. Others had one each in different categories. 

Davido earned nominations at the 2024 Grammy Awards for the following categories:

FEEL for Best Global Music Performance 
UNAVAILABLE" for Best African Performance
Timeless album for Best Global Album

snippet.title: L'apparition surprise de Céline sur la scène des Grammy Awards
snippet.description: À l'annonce de son nom, toute la salle des Grammy Awards s'est levée pour l'applaudir. "Merci à vous, je vous aime", a répondu Céline Dion. La présence de la chanteuse canadienne est un événement en lui-même, tant ses apparitions sont rares. La star canadienne a annoncé fin janvier la sortie d'un documentaire évoquant sa maladie, le syndrome de l'homme raide, qui la tient éloignée de la scène.

snippet.title: Grammy Awards Live | Taylor Swift | Trevor Noah | Miley Cyrus | Dua Lipa | Tracy Chapman | N18L
snippet.description:
Grammy Awards Red Carpet Live | 66th Grammy Awards Nominations | Grammy Awards 2024 | N18L

The stars and the best fashion moments on the red carpet of the 66TH Grammy Awards, presented this year by Trevor Noah. SZA, Phoebe Bridgers, Miley Cyrus, Taylor Swift and Olivia Rodrigo are among the top nominees..Just days before the 2024 GRAMMYs, GRAMMY U Representatives took a behind-the-scenes production tour of the Crypto.com Arena to see what it takes to run a show like Music’s Biggest Night.

Located in the heart of downtown L.A., the Crypto.com Arena has been the home of the GRAMMY Awards since 2000, and will again be host to the 66th GRAMMY Awards on Sunday, Feb. 4. Over 13,000 people are set to attend, and a crew of more than 3,500 people have been working for months behind the curtain to prepare a night of electric performances.

The exclusive tour started with a dissection of all things production as Jody Kolozsvari — Associate Producer of the GRAMMYs and a GRAMMY U alum — took the RepsU around the venue to learn from a few of the crew members.

Next, Jenna Lizerbram, manager of the Recording Academy's Entertainment & Consumer Division, took the Representatives around the Recording Academy side of productions. The team shared all things GRAMMY Sunday, including a glimpse at the media center for winners and press. Recording Academy CEO Harvey Mason Jr., made a surprise appearance on the tour, and took time to share industry insights, offer career advice, and welcome GRAMMY U Reps to the music family that is the Recording Academy. 

#grammyawards #grammyawardwinner #englishnewslive #news18live 

n18oc_world

snippet.title: Grammys 2024 Moments You Can't Miss |⭐ OSSA
snippet.description:
Join us on a star-studded journey through the 66th Grammy Awards! 
From Miley Cyrus's historic first win to Trevor Noah's enchanting hosting, and the emotional triumphs of Taylor Swift securing FOUR Album Of The Year Grammys - this recap has it all! 

Dive into the red carpet glitz with daring outfits from Miley, Halle Bailey, Heidi Klum, Paris Jackson, and the show-stealer Doja Cat!  
The Grammys 2024 weren't just about awards; they were a celebration of family, with adorable moments from Kelly Clarkson, Billy Joel, Jay Z, and more! 

Witness the legendary Celine Dion's standing ovation and Joni Mitchell's groundbreaking Grammy performance at 80.  
The night also featured a unique tribute to music icons, including the iconic Tina Turner. 💫

Taylor Swift's historic win stole the show, making her the first artist in history to secure four Grammys for Album Of The Year! 
Share your thoughts on this monumental achievement and tell us who owned your Grammy 2024 night!

snippet.title: Những Ca Khúc/Album Của Năm tại Giải Thưởng Grammy Trong 10 Năm Qua | 2015 - 2024 Grammy Awards
snippet.description:
➤ Thông tin video:
Chào mừng đến với Giải thưởng Grammy trong 10 năm qua với hạng mục Thu Âm của năm (Record of the Year), Album của năm (Album of the Year) và Bài hát của năm (Song of the Year) theo từng năm (2015-2024).

Giải Grammy là một giải thưởng âm nhạc danh giá được tổ chức hàng năm bởi Viện Hàn lâm Nghệ sĩ và Khoa học Ghi âm Quốc gia của Hoa Kỳ (National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences). Giải thưởng này tôn vinh các nghệ sĩ và tác phẩm âm nhạc xuất sắc trong nhiều thể loại khác nhau như pop, rock, rap, country, jazz, và classical,.. cũng như các lĩnh vực sản xuất, kỹ thuật và sáng tác nhạc.

▶️ Record of the Year (Bản Thu Âm của Năm): Giải này tôn vinh và ghi nhận bản thu âm đáng chú ý nhất trong năm, dựa trên cả khía cạnh sản xuất, biểu diễn và sáng tác của bản thu.

▶️ Album of the Year (Album của Năm): Đây là giải thưởng dành cho album đáng chú ý nhất trong năm, bao gồm cả khía cạnh âm nhạc và nghệ thuật, bao gồm cả sáng tác, thể loại âm nhạc, và thể loại lời bài hát.

▶️ Song of the Year (Bài Hát của Năm): Giải này tôn vinh và ghi nhận bài hát đáng chú ý nhất từ góc độ sáng tác, bất kể ai biểu diễn. Các yếu tố sáng tác và lời bài hát được đánh giá cao trong quyết định giành giải.

Giải Grammy được coi là một trong những giải thưởng âm nhạc quan trọng và uy tín nhất trên thế giới, và việc giành được một giải Grammy thường được xem là một điểm nhấn quan trọng trong sự nghiệp của một nghệ sĩ hoặc nhóm nhạc.

➤ Mạng xã hội của kênh:
- Tiktok: https://www.tiktok.com/@bxhamnhac_official
- Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/MusicChartVN

Cám ơn mọi người đã xem và theo dõi kênh Bảng Xếp Hạng Âm Nhạc.

#bxhan #grammy #hitsongs #10years

L'industrie musicale africaine, la diversité des genres et des talents du continent ne se contentent pas de conquérir les palmarès mondiaux, mais gagnent également une place sur la prestigieuse scène des Grammy. Une nouvelle catégorie des Grammy, la musique africaine, connaît une percée transformatrice, surmontant des défis structurels. snippet.title: Grammy Awards 2024: Taylor Swift, Miley Cyrus, Billie Eilish Headline Women Power; Check Winners
snippet.description:
Description: The roster of honorees at Grammy Awards 2024 boasted not only Taylor Swift and Miley Cyrus but also Indian Tabla maverick Zakir Hussain and flutist Rakesh Chaurasia, who clinched the Best Global Music Performance award. Trevor Noah, a four-time Grammy host and two-time nominee, kicked off the event with an enthusiastic greeting from Meryl Streep joke. Take a look at all the winners at Grammys 2023.
#grammys2024 #hollywood #taylorswift

snippet.title: Grammy Awards : surprise de Céline Dion et record de Taylor Swift
snippet.description:
Largement applaudie par le public, Céline Dion a créé la surprise, dimanche 4 février, lors de la cérémonie des Grammy Awards, en venant remettre un prix. Depuis la déclaration de sa maladie neurologique, qui l’avait contraint à mettre en pause sa tournée mondiale en 2020, la chanteuse québécoise ne fait que de très rares apparitions publiques.

Dimanche, elle est venue remettre le prix du meilleur album de l’année à Taylor Swift, pour Midnights. Une récompense supplémentaire pour la chanteuse américaine, qui devient l’artiste la plus récompensée pour ses albums, devant Frank Sinatra, Stevie Wonder et Paul Simon.

✅ Pour ne rien rater, abonnez-vous à la chaîne YouTube du Monde (et activez la cloche pour les notifications 🔔 !) 👉http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=LeMonde

snippet.title: GRAMMY Award Winning Songs in the Blind Auditions of The Voice
snippet.description:
The 2024 Grammy Awards are just around the corner, so we compiled the best Blind Auditions where talents sung the Record and/or Song of the Year from 2010 onwards. Unfortunately, two songs are not included because they weren’t sung in the Blind Auditions: ‘Just Like That’ by Bonnie Raitt, which won Song of the Year 2023, and ‘I Can’t Breath’ by H.E.R., which won Song of the Year 2021.
Which Blind Audition is your favorite? Let us know in the comments below👇

🚨 This video features the following performances:
00:00 Ezra Williams singing 'About Damn Time' by Lizzo, Record of the Year 2023 (Australia, 2023)
01:29 Sheer Element singing 'Leave the Door Open' by Silk Sonic, Record of the Year 2022 & Song of the Year 2022 (USA, 2023)
03:11 Wander Isaac singing 'everything i wanted' by Billie Eilish, Record of the Year 2021 (Portugal, 2022)
05:34 Thomas singing 'bad guy' by Billie Eilish, Record of the Year 2020 & Song of the Year 2020 (Vlaanderen/Belgium, 2021)
07:19 Scam Talk singing 'This Is America' by Childish Gambino, Record of the Year 2019 & Song of the Year 2019 (France, 2019)
09:31 Ashur Petersen singing '24K Magic' by Bruno Mars, Record of the Year 2018 (South Africa, 2019)
11:05 Levandé singing 'That’s What I Like' by Bruno Mars, Song of the Year 2018 (Belgique/Belgium, 2022)
12:54 Jack Vidgen singing 'Hello' by Adele, Record of the Year 2017 & Song of the Year 2017 (Australia, 2019)
14:40 Loup singing 'Uptown Funk' by Mark Ronson ft. Bruno Mars, Record of the Year 2016 (France, 2017)
16:39 Jake Shakeshaft singing 'Thinking Out Loud' by Ed Sheeran, Song of the Year 2016 (UK, 2015)
18:19 Talakai singing 'Stay with Me' by Sam Smith, Record of the Year 2015 & Song of the Year 2015 (USA, 2023)
20:16 Anna McLuckie singing 'Get Lucky' by Daft Punk ft. Pharrell Williams & Nile Rodgers, Record of the Year 2014 (UK, 2014)
22:26 Ирина Гросу singing 'Royals' by Lorde, Song of the Year 2014 (Ukraine, 2017)
24:36 Little Mess singing 'Somebody That I Used To Know' by Gotye ft. Kimbra, Record of the Year 2013 (Portugal, 2019)
27:04 Orlane Willems singing 'We Are Young' by Fun ft. Janelle Monáe, Song of the Year 2013 (Belgique/Belgium, 2021)
29:12 Michaela Husárová singing 'Rolling In The Deep' by Adele, Record of the Year 2012 & Song of the Year 2012 (Czecho Slovakia, 2019)
30:46 Maja Walentynowicz singing 'Need You Now' by Lady Antebellum, Record of the Year 2011 & Song of the Year 2011 (Poland, 2023)
32:25 Brock Ashby singing 'Use Somebody' by Kings of Leon, Record of the Year 2010 (Australia, 2018)
34:02 Elif Özcelik singing 'Single Ladies (Put a Ring on It)' by Beyoncé, Song of the Year 2010 (Germany, 2014)

https://www.tiktok.com/@TheVoiceHQ

snippet.title: History of the Grammy Awards: The Recording Academy
snippet.description:
The Grammy Awards, also known as the Grammys, are one of the most prestigious honors in the world of music. Established by the National Academy of Recording Arts and Sciences (NARAS), the Grammys have evolved over the years into one of the most prestigious honors in the world of music. In 1959, the inaugural ceremony featured 28 categories, with top honors going to artists like Ella Fitzgerald, Frank Sinatra, and Henry Mancini. In the 1960s and 1970s, the Grammys quickly gained prominence, expanding their categories to encompass a wide range of genres. In the 1980s and 1990s, the Grammys diversified to include genres such as jazz, country, and gospel. Technological advancements in the 2000s saw the inclusion of categories like Best Dance/Electronic Album and Best Rap/Sung Collaboration. In the 2010s, the Grammys embraced diversity and inclusivity, with notable moments such as Kendrick Lamar's impactful performances, Beyoncé's historic wins, and the acknowledgment of a broader spectrum of artists.
